snippet.textDisplay: Salice, You Have No Idea How Much This Video Helped Me. I'm 16 And I've Been Bi For 4 Years Now. I Recently Came Out To A Few Of My Family Members Last Year. It's Been A Year Since I've Been With My Girlfriend, And I Can Say Truthfully That My Coming Out Journey Was Nothing But Hell. The Only Person Who Doesn't Accept Me For Who I Am Is My Papa, Who I Live With. Being Young And Feeling Emotions Such As Anger, Sadness, Hurt And Betrayal From The Person You Thought Would Accept You Takes A Huge Toll On Yourself. It's Affected Me Not Only At Home But In School. I Used To Question Myself Everyday, Wondering What Was So Wrong With Me That He Would Look At Me Differently. I Even Would Tell My Girlfriend Sometimes Like Hey I Feel Terrible Because You Deserve To Be With Someone Who Can Come See You At Times And Everything. And She'd Be Like That Doesn't Matter To Me, I'll Wait As Long As I Have To. Hearing It From Her Broke My Heart Because I Had To Hide The Fact That We Were Together For Our Whole Relationship Just So I'd Be Able To Stay The Night With Her. Calling Her My Friend Didn't Feel Right. It Felt As If We Were Nothing. I Just Want You To Know That I'm So Thankful For You And The Words You Put Into This Video. It's Really Made Me Feel Like I Can Be Me Without Being Judged Or Made Fun Of Because Of The Person I'm With. I Want My Message To Go Viral, For All Of The People Out There Who Feel Like Your Not Accepted Or Feel Like You Can't Be Who You Are I Want You To Know That I Accept You. You Are Beautiful/Handsome In Your Own Ways. Don't Be Afraid To Be Yourself And Love Who You Want. Because You Have The Right To Love Whoever You Want. Gender Doesn't Matter, If You Have A Deep Affection For Someone Then So Be It. Love That Person And Don't Let Anybody Tell You Different. We Are All Fucking Fighters. We Will Get Through This Together As Long As We Keep Living Day After Day. Stay Strong Guys. I Love You Salice❤

snippet.textDisplay: I came out last year at 15 years old as lesbian I was so proud of myself cause I felt happy tht I did but then this year everything changed I was second guessing myself cause I had a lot of lesbians go from gay to bi at first I was like it’s there life but then I kept hearing from family members tht I would date men in the future and have kids allat. And I would just sit there and be like nah ion wanna do tht but then my mind started playing tricks on me got me thinkin tht I was a fake gay or I wasn’t being who I really was, it had gotten to the point where I even convinced myself tht I like men for almost 7 or more months now there was even a point in time where I wanted to commit suicide just to stop thinkin about it and Ik thts not me cause I could nevaaaaa. Also the same thing happened to my friend but she’s straight (everybody was tellin her tht she’s gay but she wasn’t) ugghhh I just wanna live my life happy and gay but it’s not easy

snippet.textDisplay: I love u girl. Your are an amazing woman & I know so many people, esp the younger ones, will benefit greatly from your body positivity & honesty about the importance of being comfortable with our own sexuality. We all have our own truth..our own identity & individual selves to explore discover & embrace. The journey thru life is difficult at best. The years of adolescence when hormones are making us crazy in ways we can't yet begin to understand;It is a vital lesson that we need to impart to our future generations, that it's ok to be who you are no matter what. That it's ok to be confused or not know exactly how to feel or what we want, desire, & ultimately are destined deep down to be. It's ok to be attracted to anyone we see as beautiful in any way for any reason. Male or female. Period. Keep being amazingly u doll!
